def: A bryozoan of the genus Flustra.
A mucilage obtained from, or containing, gun tragacanth.
Of or pertaining to a shield.A good example of these scutal monstrosities. Cussans.
One who, or that which, soothes.
A kind of light vessel used on the coast of China, having thehull built on a European model, and the rigging like that of aChinese junk. Admiral Foote.
Incrusted; covered with, or containing, crust; as, old, crustedport wine.
Growing in brackish places or in salt marches.
Produced increased vital action in the organism, or in any ofits parts.
The quality or state of being luminous; luminousness.
